args:
The prince manages to arrive in the future,
and finds a ruined world suffering under the
cruel heel of the Empire. Shocked by what he
sees, he challenges Chronos to a decisive
showdown in order to prevent the tragedy.
Is this the Halidom? It's in ruins!
What happened to us in this time?
One after the other, your allies fell in\nbattle or fled to other lands to continue\ntheir battle with the Empire.
So this hell is our future?!
Have you lost your nerve already?\nSad if so, for the true horror that\nawaits you is far worse than this.
The castle interior is in no better shape\nthan the outside. Did everyone really\nabandon it, or...
Wait. I thought I heard something...
No! Stay back! Don't come near me!
Notte, what's wrong with you?! It's me!\nIt's {player_name}!
Notte, what's going on here?\nWhat are you so afraid of?
It's okay now. I'm here, and I'll—
Yeah, right! I'm not falling for that!
You're trying to kill me just like\nyou did everyone else!
Don't act so innocent, you murderer!
This can't be. I would never...
I may be all alone now, but I'm still\ngonna get revenge!
Notte, this is not the prince you know.
That sounds like a huge pile of bull,\nso you better explain right freakin' NOW!
...Wait, so he traveled through time?\nPeople can DO that?!

I know it seems impossible, so I
understand if you do not believe.
But I assure you, we have no intention
of bringing you harm.
It's no trick, Notte. Please believe me.
How CAN I believe you after everything\nyou put them through?!
I can't believe you've become so angry...
Enough. It would seem the time\nfor talk is ended.
How have you come here, my liege?\nAnd how did...?
He intends to follow along her chain of\ncausality to a point in time where a\nformer version of you exists.
Back to when we first met...
Fly, Notte! We'll hold him off!
Go, Notte. We will not let Chronos have\nyou this day.
Ah. All has been made clear now.
Your interference here can only mean\ncausality has been altered in some\nother time.
This means I was able to\naccomplish my objective!
One day, you will be my liege for true.
There is no need to change the future.\nI have seen it, and it is GLORIOUS.

If you stop me here, you will cast yourself
down a path with an unknown destination.
You would be casting aside the glory
and honor I have seen you seize.
Thus, I bid you carry out your role\nas a vessel.
I refuse. Whatever glory awaits me in this\ntime isn't one I earned for myself.
I will be the one to decide what my future\nholds, no matter what it may be.
A foolish decision. But so be it.
Prepare yourself, vessel, for I shall scatter\nyou across the very winds of time!
And I won't either. Here and now,\nChronos, I'm going to defeat you\nand take control of my own future!
